# Caddy reverse proxy with automatic Let's Encrypt TLS.
# Replaces Traefik (whose Docker-socket provider is incompatible with Docker
# Engine 29 — it pins API 1.24, below the daemon's 1.40 minimum). Caddy does
# not use the Docker API at all; it reaches the app containers by name over the
# shared `traefik-public` network and preserves the original Host header (which
# the backend's TrustedHostMiddleware requires).
